@startuml
title One-to-One Voice Call Establishment

actor "User (Caller)" as CallerUser
participant "Call Engine" as CallEngine
participant "One-to-One Call\n(Caller)" as CallerCall
participant "Call Delegate" as CallDelegate
participant "Request Sender" as ReqSender
participant "Protocol Engine" as ProtoEngine
participant "Telegram Server" as TgServer
participant "One-to-One Call\n(Callee)" as CalleeCall
participant "Media Controller" as MediaCtrl
participant "Call Panel" as CallPanel
actor "User (Callee)" as CalleeUser

== Caller: Initiation ==

CallerUser -> CallEngine : initiate outgoing call
CallEngine -> ProtoEngine : fetch Diffie-Hellman configuration
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : get DH configuration
TgServer --> ProtoEngine : DH parameters (prime, generator)
ProtoEngine --> CallEngine : DH configuration available

CallEngine -> CallEngine : request microphone and camera permissions
CallEngine -> CallerCall : create One-to-One Call\n(waiting-for-user-confirmation state)
CallerCall -> CallerCall : transition to requesting state

== Caller: DH Public Value Generation and Request-Call ==

CallerCall -> CallDelegate : obtain Diffie-Hellman configuration
CallDelegate --> CallerCall : DH parameters

CallerCall -> CallerCall : generate secret power
CallerCall -> CallerCall : compute DH public value
CallerCall -> CallerCall : compute hash of public value

CallerCall -> ReqSender : send request-call\n(public-value hash, protocol layers, library versions)
ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : dispatch request
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : request-call (public-value hash, protocol info)
TgServer --> ProtoEngine : waiting call (call ID, access hash)
ProtoEngine --> ReqSender : protocol response
ReqSender --> CallerCall : call created (call ID, access hash)
CallerCall -> CallerCall : transition to waiting state
CallerCall -> CallerCall : start receive-timeout timer

== Callee: Incoming Call Arrives ==

TgServer -> ProtoEngine : push phone-call-requested update
ProtoEngine -> CallEngine : route update
CallEngine -> CalleeCall : create incoming One-to-One Call\n(waiting-incoming state)
note right of CalleeCall
  Stores: call ID, access hash,
  caller public-value hash
end note

CalleeCall -> ReqSender : send received-call acknowledgement
ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : dispatch request
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : received-call
CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : start ring timer
CalleeCall -> CallPanel : display incoming call notification
CallPanel -> CalleeUser : ring and show incoming call

== Caller: Ringing State ==

TgServer -> ProtoEngine : push call-waiting update (receive date)
ProtoEngine -> CallEngine : route update
CallEngine -> CallerCall : deliver waiting update
CallerCall -> CallerCall : transition to ringing state
CallerCall -> CallDelegate : play ring sound
note right of CallDelegate
  Call Delegate uses Audio Player
  to play the ring sound
end note

== Callee: User Answers ==

CalleeUser -> CallPanel : answer call
CallPanel -> CalleeCall : user accepted
CalleeCall -> CallDelegate : check microphone and camera permissions
CallDelegate --> CalleeCall : permissions granted
CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : transition to exchanging-keys state
CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : generate DH public value

CalleeCall -> ReqSender : send accept-call (callee public value)
ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : dispatch request
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : accept-call (callee public value)

note over CalleeCall
  DH config deferral: if DH configuration
  is not yet available when user answers,
  the accept-call is deferred until
  the configuration arrives
end note

== Caller: Receives Accepted, Derives Key and Confirms ==

TgServer -> ProtoEngine : push call-accepted update\n(callee public value)
ProtoEngine -> CallEngine : route update
CallEngine -> CallerCall : deliver accepted update
CallerCall -> CallerCall : validate callee public value fields
CallerCall -> CallerCall : derive shared authorization key\n(callee public value raised to caller secret power\nmodulo the DH prime)
CallerCall -> CallerCall : compute Key Fingerprint
note right of CallerCall
  Key Fingerprint is the fingerprint hash
  of the shared authorization key and the
  caller public value, rendered as an emoji
  sequence for out-of-band verification
  by both parties
end note

CallerCall -> ReqSender : send confirm-call\n(caller DH public value, Key Fingerprint)
ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : dispatch request
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : confirm-call (caller public value, fingerprint)
TgServer --> ProtoEngine : confirmed phone call\n(relay endpoints, STUN/TURN)
ProtoEngine --> ReqSender : protocol response
ReqSender --> CallerCall : call confirmed with endpoints

== Caller: Start Media Controller and Transition to Established ==

CallerCall -> MediaCtrl : create and start Media Controller\n(shared key, relay endpoints,\nSTUN/TURN, protocol layer, media-device config)
MediaCtrl -> MediaCtrl : establish real-time audio path\nover WebRTC transport
CallerCall -> CallerCall : transition to established state
CallerCall -> CallPanel : show active call\nwith emoji Key Fingerprint
CallPanel -> CallerUser : display active call and emoji fingerprint

== Callee: Receives Caller Public Value, Verifies Hash, Derives Key ==

TgServer -> ProtoEngine : push phone-call update\n(caller public value, relay endpoints)
ProtoEngine -> CallEngine : route update
CallEngine -> CalleeCall : deliver phone-call update

CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : compute hash of received caller public value
CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : compare hash against stored\ncaller public-value hash

alt hash matches
    CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : derive shared authorization key\n(caller public value raised to callee secret power\nmodulo the DH prime)
    CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : compute Key Fingerprint
    CalleeCall -> MediaCtrl : create and start Media Controller\n(shared key, relay endpoints,\nSTUN/TURN, protocol layer, media-device config)
    MediaCtrl -> MediaCtrl : establish real-time audio path\nover WebRTC transport
    CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : transition to established state
    CalleeCall -> CallPanel : show active call\nwith emoji Key Fingerprint
    CallPanel -> CalleeUser : display active call and emoji fingerprint
else hash mismatch
    CalleeCall -> CalleeCall : fail call (public-value hash mismatch)
    CalleeCall -> ReqSender : send discard-call (internal error reason)
    ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : dispatch request
    ProtoEngine -> TgServer : discard-call
end

== Active Call: Signaling Relay ==

MediaCtrl -> ReqSender : emit outgoing signaling payload
ReqSender -> ProtoEngine : send-signaling request
ProtoEngine -> TgServer : signaling data (opaque payload)
TgServer -> ProtoEngine : push signaling-data update (peer payload)
ProtoEngine -> CallEngine : route signaling update
CallEngine -> MediaCtrl : deliver incoming signaling payload

MediaCtrl -> CallPanel : report audio/video state changes,\nsignal-bar and battery level updates

== End Cases and Error Handling ==

note over CallerCall, CalleeCall
  Discard-update end cases:
  - hangup: end call normally
  - missed or declined: send discard reason to server. if need-rating flag set, show rating box and send set-rating request
  - busy: transition to busy state
  - disconnect: end call with disconnect reason
  - migrate-to-conference: switch main data-centre Group Call and join conference
end note

note over CallerCall
  Request errors or failure to derive
  the shared authorization key transition
  the call to the failed state
end note

@enduml
